> Cramfs is ugly, but JFFS over compressed loopback is not the answer.
JFFS over loopback is not even possible. JFFS doesn't work on block devices.
> Philipp Rumpf did a compression hack for JFFS so you can just run pure
> JFFS over MTD. 
Prumpf's compression for JFFS isn't so much of a hack - JFFS was actually 
designed with the idea that compression would be added. 
> For an embedded box combine that with RAMFS and you can
